			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2022</a> paper:</span><br><i>BatakJava: An Object-Oriented Programming Language with Versions</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/LuthfanAnsharLubis.html">Luthfan Anshar Lubis</a>, <a href="../profile/YudaiTanabe.html">Yudai Tanabe</a>, <a href="../profile/TomoyukiAotani.html">Tomoyuki Aotani</a>, <a href="../profile/HidehikoMasuhara.html">Hidehiko Masuhara</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3567512.3567531">10.1145/3567512.3567531</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2b.html"><span class="tagM">T2B: Evolution</span></a><ul><li> It adds first-class language support for managing multiple versions, directly addressing evolution/maintenance.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagL">T1A: Design</span></a><ul><li> The paper proposes and studies a new programming language design for versioned programming.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3d.html"><span class="tagL">T3D: GPLs</span></a><ul><li> BatakJava is a general-purpose object-oriented programming language.
</li></ul></li></ul>
